codasip:emulation.codasip:doxygen: /** * e_movi32 * * Emulation of a 32-bit immediate move. With the RISCV32I instruction set being 32-bits wide and requiring an opcode * per instruction, a 32-bit immediate cannot be stored in a single instruction. To perform this operation, it will need * to be emulate using a specific sequence of RISCV instructions per defined below. */

codasip:element.codasip:doxygen: /** * Load immediate (li) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, li rd, immediate equates to addi rd, xo, immediate */
/** * Move (mv) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, mv rd, rs equates to addi rd, rs1, 0 */
/** * NOT (not) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, not rd, rs equates to xori rd, rs1, -1 */
/** * NEG (neg) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, neg rd, rs equates to sub rd, x0, rs2 (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Set if = zero (seqz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, seqz rd, rs equates to sltiu rd, rs1, 1 */
/** * Set if |= zero (snez) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, snez rd, rs equates to sltu rd, x0, rs2 (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Set if < zero (sltz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, sltz rd, rs equates to slt rd, rs1, x0 (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Set if > zero (sgtz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, sgtz rd, rs equates to slt rd, x0, rs2 (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Set if rs1 > rs2 (setge) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, setge rd, rs1, rs2 equstes to slt rd, rs2, rs1 */
/** * Branch if = 0 (beqz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, beqz rs1, offset equates to beq rs1, x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if != 0 (bnez) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bnez rs1, offset equates to bne rs1, x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if < 0 (bltz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bltz rs1, offset equates to blt rs1, x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if < 0 (bltz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bltz rs1, offset equates to blt rs1, x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if >= 0 (bgez) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bgez rs1, offset equates to bge rs1, x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if > 0 (bgtz) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bgtz rs1, offset equates to blt x0, rs2, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Branch if rs1 > rs2 (bgt) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, bgt rs1, rs2, offset equates to blt rs2, rs1, offset */
/** * Branch if rs1 <= rs2 (ble) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, ble rs1, rs2, offset equates to bge rs2, rs1, offset */
/** * Branch if rs1 > rs2 unsigned (bgtu) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, ble rs1, rs2, offset equates to bltu rs2, rs1, offset */
/** * Branch if rs1 <= rs2 unsigned (bleu) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, ble rs1, offset equates to bgeu rs2, rs1, offset */
/** * Jump (j) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, j offset equates to jal x0, offset (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Jump Register (jr) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, jr rs equates to jalr x0, rs1, 0 */
/** * Return (ret) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, ret equates to jalr x0, ReturnReg, 0 (x0 refers register 0 which also equates to the value 0) */
/** * Call (call) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, call offset equates to jal rd, offset (rd = return register) */
/** * Call register (call_reg) pseudo instruction * In RISCV, call_reg rs equates to jalr return_register, rs1, offset (offset = 0) */
